Creating a New Project with Azure Boards

Live Demo starts here:
1. dev.azure.com pe jaake apni Organization select karo
2. New Project → Name do (e.g., AzureBoardsDemo)
3. Visibility: Private (default) ya Public
4. Version Control: Git select karo
5. Work Item Process: Yahan Basic select karta hai Piyush pehle demo ke liye
6. Project banne ke baad left sidebar mein Boards section dikhta hai:
- Work Items
- Boards (Kanban)
- Backlogs
- Sprints
- Queries
- Delivery Plans
- Analytics

Adding Work Items and Tasks
Basic Process pe demo:
1. Work Items → New Work Item
2. Type select karo: Epic, Issue, ya Task
3. Details fill karo:
Title: "Setup CI/CD Pipeline"
Assigned To: Team member select karo
State: New → Active → Resolved → Closed
Priority: 1 (Critical) se 4 (Low) tak
Tags: backend, urgent, sprint-1 jaise labels
Description: Detail mein kya karna hai
Acceptance Criteria: Kya complete hone pe yeh "done" maana jayega

Parent-Child linking:
Epic ke andar Issues add karo
Issue ke andar Tasks add karo
Isse hierarchy dikh jaati hai
Piyush batata hai: Real mein ek Issue ke andar 3-5 Tasks hote hain. Har task ko alag bande assign karo.


Understanding Iterations and Sprints
Iteration = Sprint ka Azure DevOps naam
1. Project Settings → Boards → Iterations
2. Yahan team ka Iteration Path structure banate hain:

plain
MyProject
└── Sprint 1 (Dates: 1 Jan - 14 Jan)
└── Sprint 2 (Dates: 15 Jan - 28 Jan)
└── Sprint 3 (Dates: 29 Jan - 11 Feb)

3. Har iteration ka start date aur end date set karna padta hai.
4. Team Settings mein jaake select karo kaunse sprints active hain.

Backlog mein kaise kaam karta hai:

- Backlog = Saara future ka kaam jo abhi nahi ho raha
- Jab Sprint start karo, toh Backlog se items uthake active Sprint mein daalte ho
- Sprint ke end mein jo bacha hai, woh ya toh next sprint mein jaata hai ya backlog mein reh jaata hai
